# Testing

- Add or update tests when modifying critical functionality
- Prefer React Testing Library for component behavior
- Test what users see and do — not implementation details
- Avoid brittle tests tied to internal state or class names

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — tests implementation detail
expect(wrapper.state("count")).toBe(1);

// ✅ GOOD — tests behavior
expect(screen.getByRole("button", { name: /submit/i })).toBeEnabled();
```

Do not add tests for trivial or unrelated changes unless requested.
